209	// system-prompt:augment — registered by @ax/memory-strata (Phase 2B), and
210	// potentially other plugins in the future (personalization, tenant policy).
211	// Returns markdown contributions that the orchestrator prepends to the
212	// system prompt envelope before fresh-spawning the sandbox.
213	//
214	// Single-provider service hook (one registration); the orchestrator dispatches
215	// only when `bus.hasService('system-prompt:augment')`. When absent, the
216	// orchestrator is a no-op — no augmentation, identical to today.
217	//
218	// Note: augmentation applies ONLY on the fresh-spawn path. The routed-into-
219	// existing-sandbox path reuses the originally-frozen `agentConfig.systemPrompt`
220	// that was baked into the runner's session at first spawn — re-augmenting
221	// mid-conversation would silently shift the prompt under the running agent,
222	// which neither matches caller expectations nor improves anything (the
223	// runner already has its prompt context).
