237	 * `unixSocketPath` are mutually exclusive — the subprocess sandbox uses the
238	 * TCP loopback form (`endpoint`); the k8s sandbox passes through the Unix
239	 * socket path so the runner-side bridge can convert it to a local TCP port
240	 * inside the sandbox. `caCertPem` is the PEM bytes; the sandbox plugin owns
241	 * "where on disk to write this." The orchestrator never knows or cares.
242	 */
